  "label": "Ashlock Store Room",
  "description": "Ashlock Store Room serves as the sealed storage annex of Sootlamp Quarters, built from slagcrete panels bolted into the hab-block’s basalt spine. Vitrified wall coatings and gasketed seams resist the city’s abrasive ash, while a grated intake and filter housing maintain a dry, dust-controlled interior. Racked shelves, lidded bins, and tether points line the walls to keep equipment secured during electrostatic surges and pressure cycling. A shielded lumen-strip casts bruise-violet highlights across scuffed surfaces, preserving the quarters’ hard-edged, decontamination-first order.",
